The Escape of Reading
Just reading [reading] is often chosen as an escape when one is tired of [decision-making] because it is an activity that does not use decision-making power, where "[progress]" is made by repeating the simple task of "following the words with the eyes and turning the pages.

　[Decision fatigue]
　[Reading too much makes you lose the ability to think].
　　I suppose this means that by escaping from "thinking" and "reading books of a difficulty level that requires thinking" and reading many "books that can be read without thinking" and being satisfied with that progress, we lose the opportunity to develop the ability to think
